# Cursor Rules Organization

## Directory Structure

```
.cursor/rules/
├── backend/
│   ├── api/          # FastAPI endpoints, middleware, routing
│   ├── database/     # Supabase, RLS, CRUD
│   ├── agents/       # AI agent patterns
│   └── patterns/     # Singleton, DI, etc.
├── frontend/
│   ├── architecture/ # Feature modules, state, routing
│   ├── components/   # Component patterns
│   ├── hooks/        # Custom hooks
│   └── services/     # API clients, integrations
└── meta/             # Project-wide rules
```

## File Conventions

- Use kebab-case with .mdc extension
- Place in most appropriate category folder
- Never in project root or directly in .cursor/rules/

## Rule File Structure

```markdown
---
description: Short rule description
globs: optional/path/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---

# Rule Title

Content with:

1. Instructions
2. Code examples
3. Guidelines
```

## Token Efficiency Standards

All rules MUST be token-efficient:

**Preserve:**

- Critical context for rule effectiveness
- Essential code examples
- Key distinctions between patterns

**Eliminate:**

- Redundant explanations
- Verbose descriptions
- Duplicate information
- Filler words and unnecessary elaboration

**Structure:**

- Use headings for quick scanning
- Group related items in lists
- Keep examples focused and minimal
- Favor concise over verbose
